name: Bighorn Canyon (South Fork)
description:
THIS IS DAY ONE OF A THREE DAY BACKPACK, AND DESCENT THIS UNKNOWN FORK(S) OF BIGHORN CANYON. THE PHOTO IS JARED JUST STARTING A 250 FOOT RAPPEL. PACK WEIGHED 66 POUNDS AT THE START WITH ALL THE WATER FOR THREE DAYS

Approach

WE STARTED ALONG THE RIDGELINE AT THE 7500' LEVEL AND DESCENDED(AND RE-CLIMBED) UP THREE DIFFERENT FORKS OVER A THREE DAY PERIOD. anD COVERED OVER TWENTY MILES. aND HAD A VERTICAL LOSS OF OVER 10,000 FEET DOING IT. wILD ADVENTURE INTO A SELDOM TRAVELED AREA.
